WEBVTT

00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:29.980
James, a servant of God and of the

00:00:29.980 --> 00:00:34.840
Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve tribes which are scattered abroad, greeting.

00:00:36.120 --> 00:00:43.220
My brethren, count it all joy when ye fall into diverse temptations, knowing this, that

00:00:43.220 --> 00:00:45.580
the trying of your faith worketh patience.

00:00:46.260 --> 00:00:52.100
But let patience have her perfect work, that ye may be perfect and entire, wanting nothing.

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:59.060
If any of you lack wisdom, let him ask of God, that giveth to all men liberally, and

00:00:59.060 --> 00:01:08.820
But let him ask in faith nothing wavering, for he that wavereth is like a wave of the

00:01:08.820 --> 00:01:11.420
sea driven with the wind and tossed.

00:01:12.600 --> 00:01:17.580
For let not that man think that he shall receive any thing of the Lord.

00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:23.040
A double-minded man is unstable in all his ways.

00:01:23.720 --> 00:01:31.300
Let the brother of low degree rejoice in that he is exalted, but the rich in that he is

00:01:31.300 --> 00:01:36.420
made low, because as the flower of the grass he shall pass away.

00:01:37.560 --> 00:01:43.260
For the sun is no sooner risen with a burning heat, but it withereth the grass, and the

00:01:43.260 --> 00:01:49.120
flower thereof falleth, and the grace of the fashion of it perisheth, so also shall the

00:01:49.120 --> 00:01:51.280
rich man fade away in his ways.

00:01:52.060 --> 00:01:57.660
Blessed is the man that endureth temptation, for when he is tried, he shall receive the

00:01:57.660 --> 00:02:02.160
crown of life, which the Lord hath promised to them that love him.

00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:06.780
Let no man say when he is tempted, I am tempted of God.

00:02:07.440 --> 00:02:11.800
For God cannot be tempted with evil, neither tempteth he any man.

00:02:12.580 --> 00:02:17.080
But every man is tempted when he is drawn away of his own lust and enticed.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:26.480
Then, when lust hath conceived, it bringeth forth sin, and sin, when it is finished, bringeth

00:02:26.480 --> 00:02:27.380
forth death.

00:02:28.080 --> 00:02:30.600
Do not err, my beloved brethren.

00:02:31.800 --> 00:02:37.740
Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and cometh down from the Father

00:02:37.740 --> 00:02:42.620
of lights, with whom is no variableness neither shadow of turning.

00:02:43.600 --> 00:02:49.640
Of his own will begat he us with the word of truth, that we should be a kind of first

00:02:49.640 --> 00:02:51.100
fruits of his creatures.

00:02:52.240 --> 00:02:58.800
Wherefore, my beloved brethren, let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, slow

00:02:58.800 --> 00:02:59.520
to wrath.

00:03:00.260 --> 00:03:04.040
For the wrath of man worketh not the righteousness of God.

00:03:05.220 --> 00:03:12.080
Wherefore, lay apart all filthiness and superfluity of naughtiness, and receive with meekness

00:03:12.080 --> 00:03:15.880
the engrafted word which is able to save your souls.

00:03:16.620 --> 00:03:21.780
But be ye doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving your own selves.

00:03:22.560 --> 00:03:28.140
For if any be a hearer of the word and not a doer, he is likened to a man beholding his

00:03:28.140 --> 00:03:30.160
natural face in a glass.

00:03:30.820 --> 00:03:36.740
For he beholdeth himself and goeth his way, and straightway forgetteth what manner of

00:03:36.740 --> 00:03:37.600
man he was.

00:03:38.240 --> 00:03:44.280
But whoso looketh into the perfect law of liberty, and continueth therein, he being

00:03:44.280 --> 00:03:49.420
not a forgetful hearer, but a doer of the work, this man shall be blessed in his deed.

00:03:50.380 --> 00:03:56.160
If any man among you seem to be religious, and bridleth not his tongue, but deceiveth

00:03:56.160 --> 00:03:59.820
his own heart, this man's religion is vain.

00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:07.160
Pure religion and undefiled before God and the Father is this, to visit the fatherless

00:04:07.160 --> 00:04:12.400
and widows in their affliction, and to keep himself unspotted from the world.

00:04:15.840 --> 00:04:21.860
My brethren, have not the faith of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory, with respect

00:04:21.860 --> 00:04:22.600
of persons.

00:04:23.260 --> 00:04:28.480
For if there come into your assembly a man with a gold ring and goodly apparel, and there

00:04:28.480 --> 00:04:34.860
come in also a poor man in vile raiment, and ye have respect to him that weareth the gay

00:04:34.860 --> 00:04:40.680
clothing, and say unto him, Sit thou here in a good place, and say to the poor, Stand

00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:44.300
thou there, or sit here under my footstool.

00:04:45.120 --> 00:04:50.260
Are ye not then partial in yourselves, and are become judges of evil thoughts?

00:04:51.300 --> 00:04:57.100
Harken, my beloved brethren, hath not God chosen the poor of this world, rich in faith,

00:04:57.400 --> 00:05:01.140
and heirs of the kingdom which he hath promised to them that love him?

00:05:02.040 --> 00:05:04.300
But ye have despised the poor.

00:05:05.800 --> 00:05:10.240
Do not rich men oppress you and draw you before the judgment-seats?

00:05:10.880 --> 00:05:15.240
Do not they blaspheme that worthy name by which ye are called?

00:05:16.340 --> 00:05:21.320
If ye fulfill the royal law according to the scripture, Thou shalt love thy neighbor as

00:05:21.320 --> 00:05:23.420
thyself, ye do well.

00:05:23.760 --> 00:05:30.520
But if ye have respect to persons, ye commit sin, and are convinced of the law as transgressors.

00:05:31.660 --> 00:05:38.000
For whoever shall keep the whole law, and yet offend in one point, he is guilty of all.

00:05:38.900 --> 00:05:43.880
For he that said, Do not commit adultery, said also, Do not kill.

00:05:44.640 --> 00:05:50.460
Now if thou commit no adultery, yet if thou kill, thou art become a transgressor of the

00:05:50.460 --> 00:05:50.940
law.

00:05:51.580 --> 00:05:56.700
So speak ye, and so do, as they that shall be judged by the law of liberty.

00:05:57.080 --> 00:06:01.020
For he shall have judgment without mercy that hath showed no mercy.

00:06:01.840 --> 00:06:04.700
And mercy rejoiceth against judgment.

00:06:05.740 --> 00:06:11.160
What doth it profit, my brethren, though a man say he hath faith, and have not works?

00:06:11.520 --> 00:06:12.860
Can faith save him?

00:06:13.800 --> 00:06:19.240
If a brother or sister be naked and destitute of daily food, and one of you saying to them,

00:06:19.420 --> 00:06:22.460
Depart in peace, be ye warmed and filled.

00:06:23.580 --> 00:06:28.080
Notwithstanding ye give them not those things which are needful to the body, what doth

00:06:28.080 --> 00:06:28.820
it profit?

00:06:30.220 --> 00:06:35.220
Even so faith, if it hath not works, is dead, being alone.

00:06:36.340 --> 00:06:39.540
Yea, a man shall say, Thou hast faith, and I have works.

00:06:39.900 --> 00:06:44.500
Show me thy faith without thy works, and I will show thee my faith by my works.

00:06:45.940 --> 00:06:49.460
Thou believest that there is one God, thou doest well.

00:06:49.460 --> 00:06:51.800
The devils also believe and tremble.

00:06:52.500 --> 00:06:56.920
But wilt thou know, O vain man, that faith without works is dead?

00:06:57.980 --> 00:07:03.740
Was not Abraham our father justified by works when he had offered Isaac his son upon the

00:07:03.740 --> 00:07:04.060
altar?

00:07:05.600 --> 00:07:10.760
Seest thou how faith wrought with his works, and by works was faith made perfect?

00:07:11.540 --> 00:07:17.760
And the scripture was fulfilled, which saith, Abraham believed God, and it was imputed unto

00:07:17.760 --> 00:07:22.040
him for righteousness, and he was called the friend of God.

00:07:23.260 --> 00:07:28.500
Ye see then how that by works a man is justified, and not by faith only.

00:07:29.560 --> 00:07:35.600
Likewise also was not Rahab the harlot justified by works, when she had received the messengers

00:07:35.600 --> 00:07:37.880
and had sent them out another way?

00:07:38.760 --> 00:07:44.860
For as the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without works is dead also.

00:07:48.920 --> 00:07:54.860
My brethren, be not many masters, knowing that we shall receive the greater condemnation.

00:07:55.460 --> 00:07:57.620
For in many things we offend all.

00:07:58.160 --> 00:08:04.580
If any man offend not in word, the same is a perfect man, and able also to bridle the

00:08:04.580 --> 00:08:05.240
whole body.

00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:12.660
Behold, we put bits, in the horses' mouths, that they may obey us, and we turn about their

00:08:12.660 --> 00:08:13.340
whole body.

00:08:14.040 --> 00:08:19.880
Behold also the ships, which though they be so great, and are driven of fierce winds,

00:08:20.320 --> 00:08:25.800
yet are they turned about with a very small helm, whithersoever the Governor listeth.

00:08:26.880 --> 00:08:31.820
Even so the tongue is a little member, and boasteth great things.

00:08:32.360 --> 00:08:36.300
Behold how great a matter a little fire kindleth.

00:08:36.840 --> 00:08:43.320
And the tongue is a fire, a world of iniquity, so is the tongue among our members, that it

00:08:43.320 --> 00:08:48.980
defileth the whole body, and setteth on fire the course of nature, and it is set on fire

00:08:48.980 --> 00:08:49.720
of hell.

00:08:50.760 --> 00:08:55.900
For every kind of beasts, and of birds, and of serpents, and of things in the sea, is

00:08:55.900 --> 00:08:58.720
tamed, and hath been tamed of mankind.

00:08:59.460 --> 00:09:05.580
But the tongue can no man tame, it is an unruly evil, full of deadly poison.

00:09:06.700 --> 00:09:13.060
Therewith bless we God, even the Father, and therewith curse we men, which are made after

00:09:13.060 --> 00:09:14.580
the similitude of God.

00:09:15.480 --> 00:09:19.040
Out of the same mouth proceedeth blessing and cursing.

00:09:19.680 --> 00:09:23.680
My brethren, these things ought not so to be.

00:09:24.520 --> 00:09:27.840
Doth the fountain send forth at the same time sweet water and bitter?

00:09:28.900 --> 00:09:31.560
Can the fig-tree, my brethren, bear olive-berries?

00:09:32.260 --> 00:09:37.580
Either a vine figs, so can no fountain both yield salt-water and fresh.

00:09:38.340 --> 00:09:42.700
Who is a wise man, and imbued with knowledge among you?

00:09:43.280 --> 00:09:47.860
Let him show out of a good conversation his works with meekness of wisdom.

00:09:48.560 --> 00:09:54.260
But if ye have bitter envying and strife in your hearts, glory not, and lie not against

00:09:54.260 --> 00:09:54.860
the truth.

00:09:55.720 --> 00:10:01.400
This wisdom descendeth not from above, but is earthly, sensual, devilish.

00:10:01.660 --> 00:10:07.040
For where envying and strife is, there is confusion in every evil work.

00:10:07.580 --> 00:10:14.300
But the wisdom that is from above is first purer, then peaceable, gentle, and easy to

00:10:14.300 --> 00:10:20.820
be entreated, full of mercy and good fruits without partiality and without hypocrisy.

00:10:21.420 --> 00:10:26.560
And the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace of them that make peace.

00:10:30.660 --> 00:10:33.760
From whence come wars and fighting among you?

00:10:34.420 --> 00:10:38.900
Come they not hence, even of your lusts, that war in your members?

00:10:39.640 --> 00:10:41.420
Ye lust and have not.

00:10:42.060 --> 00:10:45.560
Ye kill and desire to have, and cannot obtain.

00:10:45.980 --> 00:10:50.140
Ye fight and war, yet ye have not, because ye ask not.

00:10:50.840 --> 00:10:57.880
Ye ask and receive not, because ye ask amiss, that ye may consume it upon your lusts.

00:10:58.300 --> 00:11:04.460
Ye adulterers and adulteresses, know ye not that the friendship of the world is enmity

00:11:04.460 --> 00:11:05.160
with God?

00:11:05.960 --> 00:11:09.740
Whosoever therefore will be a friend of the world is the enemy of God.

00:11:10.600 --> 00:11:17.320
Do ye think that the scripture saith in vain, The spirit that dwelleth in us lusteth to

00:11:17.320 --> 00:11:17.620
envy?

00:11:18.380 --> 00:11:20.520
But he giveth more grace.

00:11:21.020 --> 00:11:26.580
Wherefore he saith, God resisteth the proud, but giveth grace unto the humble.

00:11:27.600 --> 00:11:33.180
Submit yourselves therefore to God, resist the devil, and he will flee from you.

00:11:33.760 --> 00:11:36.460
Draw nigh to God, and he will draw nigh to you.

00:11:37.100 --> 00:11:41.880
Cleanse your hands, ye sinners, and purify your hearts, ye double-minded.

00:11:42.880 --> 00:11:45.460
Be afflicted, and mourn, and weep.

00:11:45.760 --> 00:11:49.280
Let your laughter be turned to mourning, and your joy to heaviness.

00:11:49.880 --> 00:11:54.140
Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and he shall lift you up.

00:11:55.140 --> 00:11:57.560
Speak not evil one of another, brethren.

00:11:58.360 --> 00:12:03.860
He that speaketh evil of his brother, and judgeth his brother, speaketh evil of the

00:12:03.860 --> 00:12:06.080
law, and judgeth the law.

00:12:06.720 --> 00:12:10.440
But if thou judgest the law, thou art not a doer of the law, but a judge.

00:12:11.020 --> 00:12:14.980
There is one law-giver who is able to save and to destroy.

00:12:15.560 --> 00:12:17.840
Who art thou that judgest another?

00:12:18.820 --> 00:12:24.980
Go to now, ye that say, Today or to-morrow we will go into such a city, and continue

00:12:24.980 --> 00:12:27.880
there a year, and buy and sell, and get gain.

00:12:28.620 --> 00:12:31.720
Whereas ye know not what shall be on the morrow.

00:12:32.060 --> 00:12:33.420
For what is your life?

00:12:33.880 --> 00:12:38.400
It is even a vapor that appearth for a little time, and then vanisheth away.

00:12:39.090 --> 00:12:45.500
For that ye ought to say, If the Lord will, we shall live, and do this or that.

00:12:46.160 --> 00:12:50.540
But now ye rejoice in your boasting, all such rejoicing is evil.

00:12:51.220 --> 00:12:57.220
Therefore to him that knoweth to do good, and doeth it not, to him it is sin.

00:13:00.140 --> 00:13:05.540
Go to now, ye rich men, weep and howl for your miseries that shall come upon you.

00:13:05.540 --> 00:13:09.380
Your riches are corrupted, and your garments are moth-eaten.

00:13:09.900 --> 00:13:14.800
Your gold and silver is cankered, and the rust of them shall be a witness against you,

00:13:14.800 --> 00:13:17.120
and shall eat your flesh as it were fire.

00:13:17.540 --> 00:13:21.100
Ye have heaped treasure together for the last days.

00:13:21.980 --> 00:13:26.100
Behold, the hire of the laborers who have reaped down your fields,

00:13:26.500 --> 00:13:29.600
which is of you kept back by fraud, cryeth.

00:13:29.780 --> 00:13:34.600
And the cries of them which have reaped are entered into the ears of the Lord of Sabaoth.

00:13:34.600 --> 00:13:38.500
Ye have lived in pleasure on the earth and been wanton.

00:13:39.640 --> 00:13:42.420
Ye have nourished your hearts, as in a day of slaughter.

00:13:42.860 --> 00:13:47.500
Ye have condemned and killed the just, and he doth not resist you.

00:13:48.240 --> 00:13:51.380
Be patient therefore, brethren, unto the coming of the Lord.

00:13:51.960 --> 00:13:55.620
Behold, the husbandman waiteth for the precious fruit of the earth,

00:13:56.000 --> 00:14:01.020
and hath long patience for it, until he receive the early and latter rain.

00:14:01.980 --> 00:14:07.480
Be ye also patient, establish your hearts, for the coming of the Lord draweth nigh.

00:14:08.560 --> 00:14:12.220
Grudge not one against another, brethren, lest ye be condemned.

00:14:12.960 --> 00:14:15.940
Behold, the judge standeth before the door.

00:14:16.840 --> 00:14:20.700
Take, my brethren, the prophets, who have spoken in the name of the Lord,

00:14:21.080 --> 00:14:24.280
for an example of suffering affliction and of patience.

00:14:25.100 --> 00:14:27.860
Behold, we count them happy which endure.

00:14:28.540 --> 00:14:32.600
Ye have heard of the patience of Job, and have seen the end of the Lord,

00:14:33.040 --> 00:14:36.280
that the Lord is very pitiful and of tender mercy.

00:14:36.980 --> 00:14:42.280
But above all things, my brethren, swear not, neither by heaven, neither by the earth,

00:14:42.600 --> 00:14:51.040
neither by any other oath, but let your yea be yea, and your nay, nay, lest ye fall into condemnation.

00:14:52.040 --> 00:14:55.520
Is any among you afflicted? Let him pray.

00:14:56.160 --> 00:14:59.800
Is any merry? Let him sing psalms.

00:15:00.460 --> 00:15:05.920
Is any sick among you? Let him call for the elders of the church, and let them pray over him,

00:15:06.340 --> 00:15:08.760
anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord.

00:15:09.440 --> 00:15:14.000
And the prayer of faith shall save the sick, and the Lord shall raise him up,

00:15:14.180 --> 00:15:18.160
and if he have committed sins, they shall be forgiven him.

00:15:19.460 --> 00:15:24.380
Confess your faults one to another, and pray one for another, that ye may be healed.

00:15:25.020 --> 00:15:29.180
The effectual fervent prayer of a righteous man availeth much.

00:15:30.360 --> 00:15:36.540
Elias was a man subject to like passions as we are, and he prayed earnestly that it might not rain,

00:15:36.640 --> 00:15:41.040
and it rained not on the earth by the space of three years and six months.

00:15:41.640 --> 00:15:46.320
And he prayed again, and the heaven gave rain, and the earth brought forth her fruit.

00:15:47.320 --> 00:15:53.560
Brethren, if any of you do err from the truth, and one convert him, let him know

00:15:53.560 --> 00:15:57.360
that he which converteth the sinner from the error of his way

00:15:57.360 --> 00:16:02.860
shall save a soul from death, and shall hide a multitude of sins.

00:16:05.740 --> 00:16:08.240
End of the Epistle of James.
